I am back on my computer now.
You have to add the requestType : 'post' to your JS configuration, not the connector configuration.
var options = {
    url  : 'php/connector.php',
    lang : 'en',
    requestType : 'post'
}
$('#elfinder').elfinder(options);
source from above
. But that is only for the connector. You still need to add it to the JS configuration, so that JS will send the information using POST instead of GET.
The connector takes any of the requests, so you have to define it in the JS configuration when you initilize elFinder.
