    rememberLastDir : false
}).elfinder('instance');
in connector.php you can access the custom data from $_GET[] and parse it to your needs. $filePath is the path where your files are stored. If startPath is null/empty, the $startParth will be the same as the $filePath.
``` php
$filePath = '../files';
$startPath = $filePath;
if(isset($_GET['startPath']) && !empty($_GET['startPath'])) {
    $startPath .= '/'.$_GET['startPath'];
}
```
in the roots array in the options array in connector.php you mst set:
php
...
'path'          => $filePath,
'startPath'  => $startPath,
...
to get everything working you also need to apply the solution from issue 157 - https://github.com/Studio-42/elFinder/issues/157
elfinder.full.js (or elfinder.min.js) must be changed from
javascript
...
lastDir : function(hash) { 
    return this.storage('lastdir', hash);
},
...
to 
javascript
...
lastDir : function(hash) { 
    return this.options.rememberLastDir ? this.storage('lastdir', hash) : '';
},
...
