. Here the function who create the filename:
```
/**** thumbnails *****/
/
 * Return thumbnail file name for required file
 *
 * @param  array  $stat  file stat
 * @return string
 * @author Dmitry (dio) Levashov
 /
protected function tmbname($stat) {
    return $stat['hash'].$stat['ts'].'.png';
}
```
Found in elFinder.Volumedriver.class.php
The array $stat is build i.e. in the elFinderVolumeLocalFileSystem.class.php in the Function _stat($path).
$stat looks like this:
$stat['mime']  = 'symlink-broken';
$stat['read']  = false;
$stat['write'] = false;
$stat['size']  = 0;
$stat['alias']  = $this->_path($target);
$stat['target'] = $target;
$stat['ts']    = filemtime($path);
In Function updateCache($path, $stat) the $stat['hash'] is filled (Found in elFinder.Volumedriver.class.php)
$stat['hash'] = $this->encode($path);

After all that foundings you finally just need array with 'hash' and 'ts' like this:
$s['ts']    = filemtime($path);
$s['hash'] = $this->encode($path);
then you have your thumbnailname $s['hash'].$s['ts'].'.png';

Other Solution could be use of gettmb($path, $stat) Function in elFinder.Volumedriver.class.php
