Just run into this issue, I was able to solve it using @D-Ne0 's suggestion. You need to create a new elFinderVolume and overwrite the upload method. For example:
```php
class elFinderVolumeCustomLocalFileSystem extends elFinderVolumeLocalFileSystem
{
    public function upload($fp, $dst, $name, $tmpname, $hashes = array())
    {
        // My code goes here
    return parent::upload($fp, $dst, $name, $tmpname, $hashes);
}

}
```
Then register the driver in your connector:
php
$opts = array(
    'roots' => array(
        array(
            'driver' => 'CustomLocalFileSystem', // ' elFinderVolume' is automatically removed
            // Other options go here
        )
    )
);
Hope this helps if anyone else stumbles on this issue....

